IPhysicalLog IPhysicalLog Interface

Definition

Namespace:
System.Fabric.Data.Log
Assembly:
Microsoft.ServiceFabric.Data.Impl.dll

An open IPhysicalLog instance is a handle abstraction that provides access and control over the corresponding system resources that make up a container for multiple separate logical log instances.

Once an application gets a reference to an opened IPhysicalLog instance, the backing physical log is already mounted (recovered) and available.

Abort() Abort()

Edit

Abort the physical log handle instance synchronously - will occur automatically thru GC if CloseAsync is not called

NOTE: Any currently opened ILogicalLog instances that were created/opened thru a current IPhysicalLog will remain open - they have an independent life-span once created.

void Abort()Sub Abort

AssignAliasAsync(Guid, String, CancellationToken) AssignAliasAsync(Guid, String, CancellationToken)

Edit

Create a named alias for a given logical log

This method asynchronously assigns a string that serves as an alias to the logicalLogId. The alias can be resolved to the logicalLogId Guid using the ResolveAliasAsync() method. The alias can be removed using the RemoveAliasAsync() method.

If the stream already has an alias that alias is overwritten.

Known Exceptions:

System.Fabric.FabricException FabricObjectClosedException
